		<div class="comment_text"><p>from the Tomcat 3.2 docs available here (<a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fjakarta.apache.org%2Ftomcat%2Ftomcat-3.2-doc%2Freadme%29%3A%3AypO-w2Yta5V46nt_3yrt8QzisuU&amp;cuid=3321886" rel="nofollow noopener" title="http://jakarta.apache.org/tomcat/tomcat-3.2-doc/readme):">http://jakarta.apache.org/t...</a></p><p>"&lt;i&gt;6.4 Automatic Servlet Reloading</p><p>Tomcat 3.2 includes a feature whereby you can ask it to automatically reload servlet classes (loaded from either the WEB-INF/classes directory<br>or a JAR file in the WEB-INF/lib directory) that have been changed.  This feature is experimental, and may not be completely functional.  In particular, changes to classes other than the servlet you are requesting do not trigger class reloads -- you will need to restart Tomcat to reflect changes in those classes.&lt;/i&gt;"</p></div>
